      • setFillBackgroundColor

        public void setFillBackgroundColor(short bg)
        set the background fill color.

        For example:

         cs.setFillPattern(HSSFCellStyle.FINE_DOTS );
 cs.setFillBackgroundColor(new HSSFColor.RED().getIndex());
        optionally a Foreground and background fill can be applied: Note: Ensure Foreground color is set prior to background 
         cs.setFillPattern(HSSFCellStyle.FINE_DOTS );
 cs.setFillForegroundColor(new HSSFColor.BLUE().getIndex());
 cs.setFillBackgroundColor(new HSSFColor.RED().getIndex());
        or, for the special case of SOLID_FILL: 
         cs.setFillPattern(HSSFCellStyle.SOLID_FOREGROUND );
 cs.setFillForegroundColor(new HSSFColor.RED().getIndex());
        It is necessary to set the fill style in order for the color to be shown in the cell.        (${t_8cf325038ced4889a48a617ebc5abf6f})
        Specified by:
        setFillBackgroundColor in interface CellStyle(${t_37084a41a4d14cb69f282e226e7868c8})
        Parameters:
        bg - color(${t_af88cf0f62f8475e81304076f0559fdd})

      • cloneStyleFrom

        public void cloneStyleFrom(CellStyle source)
        Clones all the style information from another HSSFCellStyle, onto this one. This HSSFCellStyle will then have all the same properties as the source, but the two may be edited independently. Any stylings on this HSSFCellStyle will be lost! The source HSSFCellStyle could be from another HSSFWorkbook if you like. This allows you to copy styles from one HSSFWorkbook to another.(${t_d8b8392d15474a20b669f05b34ef27ce})
